2654/* Given phi statement PHI that hides a candidate from its BASIS, find
2655 the increments along each incoming arc (recursively handling additional
2656 phis that may be present) and record them. These increments are the
2657 difference in index between the index-adjusting statements and the
2658 index of the basis. */
2659
2660static void
2661record_phi_increments (slsr_cand_t basis, gimple *phi)
2662{
2663 unsigned i;
2664 slsr_cand_t phi_cand = *stmt_cand_map->get (phi);
2665
2666 for (i = 0; i < gimple_phi_num_args (phi); i++)
2667 {
2668 tree arg = gimple_phi_arg_def (phi, i);
2669 gimple *arg_def = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (arg);
2670
2671 if (gimple_code (arg_def) == GIMPLE_PHI)
2672 record_phi_increments (basis, arg_def);
2673 else
2674 {
2675 widest_int diff;
2676
2677 if (operand_equal_p (arg, phi_cand->base_expr, 0))
2678 {
2679 diff = -basis->index;
2680 record_increment (phi_cand, diff, PHI_ADJUST);
2681 }
2682 else
2683 {
2684 slsr_cand_t arg_cand = base_cand_from_table (arg);
2685 diff = arg_cand->index - basis->index;
2686 record_increment (arg_cand, diff, PHI_ADJUST);
2687 }
2688 }
2689 }
2690}

2692/* Determine how many times each unique increment occurs in the set
2693 of candidates rooted at C's parent, recording the data in the
2694 increment vector. For each unique increment I, if an initializer
2695 T_0 = stride * I is provided by a candidate that dominates all
2696 candidates with the same increment, also record T_0 for subsequent
2697 use. */
2698
2699static void
2700record_increments (slsr_cand_t c)
2701{
2702 if (!cand_already_replaced (c))
2703 {
2704 if (!phi_dependent_cand_p (c))
2705 record_increment (c, cand_increment (c), NOT_PHI_ADJUST);
2706 else
2707 {
2708 /* A candidate with a basis hidden by a phi will have one
2709 increment for its relationship to the index represented by
2710 the phi, and potentially additional increments along each
2711 incoming edge. For the root of the dependency tree (which
2712 has no basis), process just the initial index in case it has
2713 an initializer that can be used by subsequent candidates. */
2714 record_increment (c, c->index, NOT_PHI_ADJUST);
2715
2716 if (c->basis)
2717 record_phi_increments (lookup_cand (c->basis),
2718 lookup_cand (c->def_phi)->cand_stmt);
2719 }
2720 }
2721
2722 if (c->sibling)
2723 record_increments (lookup_cand (c->sibling));
2724
2725 if (c->dependent)
2726 record_increments (lookup_cand (c->dependent));
2727}
2728
2729/* Add up and return the costs of introducing add statements that
2730 require the increment INCR on behalf of candidate C and phi
2731 statement PHI. Accumulate into *SAVINGS the potential savings
2732 from removing existing statements that feed PHI and have no other
2733 uses. */
2734
2735static int
2736phi_incr_cost (slsr_cand_t c, const widest_int &incr, gimple *phi,
2737 int *savings)
2738{
2739 unsigned i;
2740 int cost = 0;
2741 slsr_cand_t basis = lookup_cand (c->basis);
2742 slsr_cand_t phi_cand = *stmt_cand_map->get (phi);
2743
2744 for (i = 0; i < gimple_phi_num_args (phi); i++)
2745 {
2746 tree arg = gimple_phi_arg_def (phi, i);
2747 gimple *arg_def = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (arg);
2748
2749 if (gimple_code (arg_def) == GIMPLE_PHI)
2750 {
2751 int feeding_savings = 0;
2752 cost += phi_incr_cost (c, incr, arg_def, &feeding_savings);
2753 if (has_single_use (gimple_phi_result (arg_def)))
2754 *savings += feeding_savings;
2755 }
2756 else
2757 {
2758 widest_int diff;
2759 slsr_cand_t arg_cand;
2760
2761 /* When the PHI argument is just a pass-through to the base
2762 expression of the hidden basis, the difference is zero minus
2763 the index of the basis. There is no potential savings by
2764 eliminating a statement in this case. */
2765 if (operand_equal_p (arg, phi_cand->base_expr, 0))
2766 {
2767 arg_cand = (slsr_cand_t) NULL;
2768 diff = -basis->index;
2769 }
2770 else
2771 {
2772 arg_cand = base_cand_from_table (arg);
2773 diff = arg_cand->index - basis->index;
2774 }
2775
2776 if (incr == diff)
2777 {
2778 tree basis_lhs = gimple_assign_lhs (basis->cand_stmt);
2779 cost += add_cost (true, TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (basis_lhs)));
2780 if (arg_cand)
2781 {
2782 tree lhs = gimple_assign_lhs (arg_cand->cand_stmt);
2783 if (has_single_use (lhs))
2784 *savings += stmt_cost (arg_cand->cand_stmt, true);
2785 }
2786 }
2787 }
2788 }
2789
2790 return cost;
2791}

2793/* Return the first candidate in the tree rooted at C that has not
2794 already been replaced, favoring siblings over dependents. */
2795
2796static slsr_cand_t
2797unreplaced_cand_in_tree (slsr_cand_t c)
2798{
2799 if (!cand_already_replaced (c))
2800 return c;
2801
2802 if (c->sibling)
2803 {
2804 slsr_cand_t sib = unreplaced_cand_in_tree (lookup_cand (c->sibling));
2805 if (sib)
2806 return sib;
2807 }
2808
2809 if (c->dependent)
2810 {
2811 slsr_cand_t dep = unreplaced_cand_in_tree (lookup_cand (c->dependent));
2812 if (dep)
2813 return dep;
2814 }
2815
2816 return NULL;
2817}

2819/* Return TRUE if the candidates in the tree rooted at C should be
2820 optimized for speed, else FALSE. We estimate this based on the block
2821 containing the most dominant candidate in the tree that has not yet
2822 been replaced. */
2823
2824static bool
2825optimize_cands_for_speed_p (slsr_cand_t c)
2826{
2827 slsr_cand_t c2 = unreplaced_cand_in_tree (c);
2828 gcc_assert (c2);
2829 return optimize_bb_for_speed_p (gimple_bb (c2->cand_stmt));
2830}

2832/* Add COST_IN to the lowest cost of any dependent path starting at
2833 candidate C or any of its siblings, counting only candidates along
2834 such paths with increment INCR. Assume that replacing a candidate
2835 reduces cost by REPL_SAVINGS. Also account for savings from any
2836 statements that would go dead. If COUNT_PHIS is true, include
2837 costs of introducing feeding statements for conditional candidates. */
2838
2839static int
2840lowest_cost_path (int cost_in, int repl_savings, slsr_cand_t c,
2841 const widest_int &incr, bool count_phis)
2842{
2843 int local_cost, sib_cost, savings = 0;
2844 widest_int cand_incr = cand_abs_increment (c);
2845
2846 if (cand_already_replaced (c))
2847 local_cost = cost_in;
2848 else if (incr == cand_incr)
2849 local_cost = cost_in - repl_savings - c->dead_savings;
2850 else
2851 local_cost = cost_in - c->dead_savings;
2852
2853 if (count_phis
2854 && phi_dependent_cand_p (c)
2855 && !cand_already_replaced (c))
2856 {
2857 gimple *phi = lookup_cand (c->def_phi)->cand_stmt;
2858 local_cost += phi_incr_cost (c, incr, phi, &savings);
2859
2860 if (has_single_use (gimple_phi_result (phi)))
2861 local_cost -= savings;
2862 }
2863
2864 if (c->dependent)
2865 local_cost = lowest_cost_path (local_cost, repl_savings,
2866 lookup_cand (c->dependent), incr,
2867 count_phis);
2868
2869 if (c->sibling)
2870 {
2871 sib_cost = lowest_cost_path (cost_in, repl_savings,
2872 lookup_cand (c->sibling), incr,
2873 count_phis);
2874 local_cost = MIN (local_cost, sib_cost);
2875 }
2876
2877 return local_cost;
2878}
2879
2880/* Compute the total savings that would accrue from all replacements
2881 in the candidate tree rooted at C, counting only candidates with
2882 increment INCR. Assume that replacing a candidate reduces cost
2883 by REPL_SAVINGS. Also account for savings from statements that
2884 would go dead. */
2885
2886static int
2887total_savings (int repl_savings, slsr_cand_t c, const widest_int &incr,
2888 bool count_phis)
2889{
2890 int savings = 0;
2891 widest_int cand_incr = cand_abs_increment (c);
2892
2893 if (incr == cand_incr && !cand_already_replaced (c))
2894 savings += repl_savings + c->dead_savings;
2895
2896 if (count_phis
2897 && phi_dependent_cand_p (c)
2898 && !cand_already_replaced (c))
2899 {
2900 int phi_savings = 0;
2901 gimple *phi = lookup_cand (c->def_phi)->cand_stmt;
2902 savings -= phi_incr_cost (c, incr, phi, &phi_savings);
2903
2904 if (has_single_use (gimple_phi_result (phi)))
2905 savings += phi_savings;
2906 }
2907
2908 if (c->dependent)
2909 savings += total_savings (repl_savings, lookup_cand (c->dependent), incr,
2910 count_phis);
2911
2912 if (c->sibling)
2913 savings += total_savings (repl_savings, lookup_cand (c->sibling), incr,
2914 count_phis);
2915
2916 return savings;
2917}
2918
2919/* Use target-specific costs to determine and record which increments
2920 in the current candidate tree are profitable to replace, assuming
2921 MODE and SPEED. FIRST_DEP is the first dependent of the root of
2922 the candidate tree.
2923
2924 One slight limitation here is that we don't account for the possible
2925 introduction of casts in some cases. See replace_one_candidate for
2926 the cases where these are introduced. This should probably be cleaned
2927 up sometime. */
2928
2929static void
2930analyze_increments (slsr_cand_t first_dep, machine_mode mode, bool speed)
2931{
2932 unsigned i;
2933
2934 for (i = 0; i < incr_vec_len; i++)
2935 {
2936 HOST_WIDE_INT incr = incr_vec[i].incr.to_shwi ();
2937
2938 /* If somehow this increment is bigger than a HWI, we won't
2939 be optimizing candidates that use it. And if the increment
2940 has a count of zero, nothing will be done with it. */
2941 if (!wi::fits_shwi_p (incr_vec[i].incr) || !incr_vec[i].count)
2942 incr_vec[i].cost = COST_INFINITE;
2943
2944 /* Increments of 0, 1, and -1 are always profitable to replace,
2945 because they always replace a multiply or add with an add or
2946 copy, and may cause one or more existing instructions to go
2947 dead. Exception: -1 can't be assumed to be profitable for
2948 pointer addition. */
2949 else if (incr == 0
2950 || incr == 1
2951 || (incr == -1
2952 && !POINTER_TYPE_P (first_dep->cand_type)))
2953 incr_vec[i].cost = COST_NEUTRAL;
2954
2955 /* If we need to add an initializer, give up if a cast from the
2956 candidate's type to its stride's type can lose precision.
2957 Note that this already takes into account that the stride may
2958 have been cast to a wider type, in which case this test won't
2959 fire. Example:
2960
2961 short int _1;
2962 _2 = (int) _1;
2963 _3 = _2 * 10;
2964 _4 = x + _3; ADD: x + (10 * (int)_1) : int
2965 _5 = _2 * 15;
2966 _6 = x + _5; ADD: x + (15 * (int)_1) : int
2967
2968 Although the stride was a short int initially, the stride
2969 used in the analysis has been widened to an int, and such
2970 widening will be done in the initializer as well. */
2971 else if (!incr_vec[i].initializer
2972 && TREE_CODE (first_dep->stride) != INTEGER_CST
2973 && !legal_cast_p_1 (first_dep->stride_type,
2974 TREE_TYPE (gimple_assign_lhs
2975 (first_dep->cand_stmt))))
2976 incr_vec[i].cost = COST_INFINITE;
2977
2978 /* If we need to add an initializer, make sure we don't introduce
2979 a multiply by a pointer type, which can happen in certain cast
2980 scenarios. */
2981 else if (!incr_vec[i].initializer
2982 && TREE_CODE (first_dep->stride) != INTEGER_CST
2983 && POINTER_TYPE_P (first_dep->stride_type))
2984 incr_vec[i].cost = COST_INFINITE;
2985
2986 /* For any other increment, if this is a multiply candidate, we
2987 must introduce a temporary T and initialize it with
2988 T_0 = stride * increment. When optimizing for speed, walk the
2989 candidate tree to calculate the best cost reduction along any
2990 path; if it offsets the fixed cost of inserting the initializer,
2991 replacing the increment is profitable. When optimizing for
2992 size, instead calculate the total cost reduction from replacing
2993 all candidates with this increment. */
2994 else if (first_dep->kind == CAND_MULT)
2995 {
2996 int cost = mult_by_coeff_cost (incr, mode, speed);
2997 int repl_savings = mul_cost (speed, mode) - add_cost (speed, mode);
2998 if (speed)
2999 cost = lowest_cost_path (cost, repl_savings, first_dep,
3000 incr_vec[i].incr, COUNT_PHIS);
3001 else
3002 cost -= total_savings (repl_savings, first_dep, incr_vec[i].incr,
3003 COUNT_PHIS);
3004
3005 incr_vec[i].cost = cost;
3006 }
3007
3008 /* If this is an add candidate, the initializer may already
3009 exist, so only calculate the cost of the initializer if it
3010 doesn't. We are replacing one add with another here, so the
3011 known replacement savings is zero. We will account for removal
3012 of dead instructions in lowest_cost_path or total_savings. */
3013 else
3014 {
3015 int cost = 0;
3016 if (!incr_vec[i].initializer)
3017 cost = mult_by_coeff_cost (incr, mode, speed);
3018
3019 if (speed)
3020 cost = lowest_cost_path (cost, 0, first_dep, incr_vec[i].incr,
3021 DONT_COUNT_PHIS);
3022 else
3023 cost -= total_savings (0, first_dep, incr_vec[i].incr,
3024 DONT_COUNT_PHIS);
3025
3026 incr_vec[i].cost = cost;
3027 }
3028 }
3029}

3031/* Return the nearest common dominator of BB1 and BB2. If the blocks
3032 are identical, return the earlier of C1 and C2 in *WHERE. Otherwise,
3033 if the NCD matches BB1, return C1 in *WHERE; if the NCD matches BB2,
3034 return C2 in *WHERE; and if the NCD matches neither, return NULL in
3035 *WHERE. Note: It is possible for one of C1 and C2 to be NULL. */
3036
3037static basic_block
3038ncd_for_two_cands (basic_block bb1, basic_block bb2,
3039 slsr_cand_t c1, slsr_cand_t c2, slsr_cand_t *where)
3040{
3041 basic_block ncd;
3042
3043 if (!bb1)
3044 {
3045 *where = c2;
3046 return bb2;
3047 }
3048
3049 if (!bb2)
3050 {
3051 *where = c1;
3052 return bb1;
3053 }
3054
3055 ncd = nearest_common_dominator (CDI_DOMINATORS, bb1, bb2);
3056
3057 /* If both candidates are in the same block, the earlier
3058 candidate wins. */
3059 if (bb1 == ncd && bb2 == ncd)
3060 {
3061 if (!c1 || (c2 && c2->cand_num < c1->cand_num))
3062 *where = c2;
3063 else
3064 *where = c1;
3065 }
3066
3067 /* Otherwise, if one of them produced a candidate in the
3068 dominator, that one wins. */
3069 else if (bb1 == ncd)
3070 *where = c1;
3071
3072 else if (bb2 == ncd)
3073 *where = c2;
3074
3075 /* If neither matches the dominator, neither wins. */
3076 else
3077 *where = NULL;
3078
3079 return ncd;
3080}

3082/* Consider all candidates that feed PHI. Find the nearest common
3083 dominator of those candidates requiring the given increment INCR.
3084 Further find and return the nearest common dominator of this result
3085 with block NCD. If the returned block contains one or more of the
3086 candidates, return the earliest candidate in the block in *WHERE. */
3087
3088static basic_block
3089ncd_with_phi (slsr_cand_t c, const widest_int &incr, gphi *phi,
3090 basic_block ncd, slsr_cand_t *where)
3091{
3092 unsigned i;
3093 slsr_cand_t basis = lookup_cand (c->basis);
3094 slsr_cand_t phi_cand = *stmt_cand_map->get (phi);
3095
3096 for (i = 0; i < gimple_phi_num_args (phi); i++)
3097 {
3098 tree arg = gimple_phi_arg_def (phi, i);
3099 gimple *arg_def = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (arg);
3100
3101 if (gimple_code (arg_def) == GIMPLE_PHI)
3102 ncd = ncd_with_phi (c, incr, as_a <gphi *> (arg_def), ncd, where);
3103 else
3104 {
3105 widest_int diff;
3106
3107 if (operand_equal_p (arg, phi_cand->base_expr, 0))
3108 diff = -basis->index;
3109 else
3110 {
3111 slsr_cand_t arg_cand = base_cand_from_table (arg);
3112 diff = arg_cand->index - basis->index;
3113 }
3114
3115 basic_block pred = gimple_phi_arg_edge (phi, i)->src;
3116
3117 if ((incr == diff) || (!address_arithmetic_p && incr == -diff))
3118 ncd = ncd_for_two_cands (ncd, pred, *where, NULL, where);
3119 }
3120 }
3121
3122 return ncd;
3123}

3125/* Consider the candidate C together with any candidates that feed
3126 C's phi dependence (if any). Find and return the nearest common
3127 dominator of those candidates requiring the given increment INCR.
3128 If the returned block contains one or more of the candidates,
3129 return the earliest candidate in the block in *WHERE. */
3130
3131static basic_block
3132ncd_of_cand_and_phis (slsr_cand_t c, const widest_int &incr, slsr_cand_t *where)
3133{
3134 basic_block ncd = NULL;
3135
3136 if (cand_abs_increment (c) == incr)
3137 {
3138 ncd = gimple_bb (c->cand_stmt);
3139 *where = c;
3140 }
3141
3142 if (phi_dependent_cand_p (c))
3143 ncd = ncd_with_phi (c, incr,
3144 as_a <gphi *> (lookup_cand (c->def_phi)->cand_stmt),
3145 ncd, where);
3146
3147 return ncd;
3148}

3150/* Consider all candidates in the tree rooted at C for which INCR
3151 represents the required increment of C relative to its basis.
3152 Find and return the basic block that most nearly dominates all
3153 such candidates. If the returned block contains one or more of
3154 the candidates, return the earliest candidate in the block in
3155 *WHERE. */
3156
3157static basic_block
3158nearest_common_dominator_for_cands (slsr_cand_t c, const widest_int &incr,
3159 slsr_cand_t *where)
3160{
3161 basic_block sib_ncd = NULL, dep_ncd = NULL, this_ncd = NULL, ncd;
3162 slsr_cand_t sib_where = NULL, dep_where = NULL, this_where = NULL, new_where;
3163
3164 /* First find the NCD of all siblings and dependents. */
3165 if (c->sibling)
3166 sib_ncd = nearest_common_dominator_for_cands (lookup_cand (c->sibling),
3167 incr, &sib_where);
3168 if (c->dependent)
3169 dep_ncd = nearest_common_dominator_for_cands (lookup_cand (c->dependent),
3170 incr, &dep_where);
3171 if (!sib_ncd && !dep_ncd)
3172 {
3173 new_where = NULL;
3174 ncd = NULL;
3175 }
3176 else if (sib_ncd && !dep_ncd)
3177 {
3178 new_where = sib_where;
3179 ncd = sib_ncd;
3180 }
3181 else if (dep_ncd && !sib_ncd)
3182 {
3183 new_where = dep_where;
3184 ncd = dep_ncd;
3185 }
3186 else
3187 ncd = ncd_for_two_cands (sib_ncd, dep_ncd, sib_where,
3188 dep_where, &new_where);
3189
3190 /* If the candidate's increment doesn't match the one we're interested
3191 in (and nor do any increments for feeding defs of a phi-dependence),
3192 then the result depends only on siblings and dependents. */
3193 this_ncd = ncd_of_cand_and_phis (c, incr, &this_where);
3194
3195 if (!this_ncd || cand_already_replaced (c))
3196 {
3197 *where = new_where;
3198 return ncd;
3199 }
3200
3201 /* Otherwise, compare this candidate with the result from all siblings
3202 and dependents. */
3203 ncd = ncd_for_two_cands (ncd, this_ncd, new_where, this_where, where);
3204
3205 return ncd;
3206}

3208/* Return TRUE if the increment indexed by INDEX is profitable to replace. */
3209
3210static inline bool
3211profitable_increment_p (unsigned index)
3212{
3213 return (incr_vec[index].cost <= COST_NEUTRAL);
3214}
3215
3216/* For each profitable increment in the increment vector not equal to
3217 0 or 1 (or -1, for non-pointer arithmetic), find the nearest common
3218 dominator of all statements in the candidate chain rooted at C
3219 that require that increment, and insert an initializer
3220 T_0 = stride * increment at that location. Record T_0 with the
3221 increment record. */
3222
3223static void
3224insert_initializers (slsr_cand_t c)
3225{
3226 unsigned i;
3227
3228 for (i = 0; i < incr_vec_len; i++)
3229 {
3230 basic_block bb;
3231 slsr_cand_t where = NULL;
3232 gassign *init_stmt;
3233 gassign *cast_stmt = NULL;
3234 tree new_name, incr_tree, init_stride;
3235 widest_int incr = incr_vec[i].incr;
3236
3237 if (!profitable_increment_p (i)
3238 || incr == 1
3239 || (incr == -1
3240 && (!POINTER_TYPE_P (lookup_cand (c->basis)->cand_type)))
3241 || incr == 0)
3242 continue;
3243
3244 /* We may have already identified an existing initializer that
3245 will suffice. */
3246 if (incr_vec[i].initializer)
3247 {
3248 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3249 {
3250 fputs ("Using existing initializer: ", dump_file);
3251 print_gimple_stmt (dump_file,
3252 SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (incr_vec[i].initializer),
3253 0, 0);
3254 }
3255 continue;
3256 }
3257
3258 /* Find the block that most closely dominates all candidates
3259 with this increment. If there is at least one candidate in
3260 that block, the earliest one will be returned in WHERE. */
3261 bb = nearest_common_dominator_for_cands (c, incr, &where);
3262
3263 /* If the NCD is not dominated by the block containing the
3264 definition of the stride, we can't legally insert a
3265 single initializer. Mark the increment as unprofitable
3266 so we don't make any replacements. FIXME: Multiple
3267 initializers could be placed with more analysis. */
3268 gimple *stride_def = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (c->stride);
3269 basic_block stride_bb = gimple_bb (stride_def);
3270
3271 if (stride_bb && !dominated_by_p (CDI_DOMINATORS, bb, stride_bb))
3272 {
3273 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3274 fprintf (dump_file,
3275 "Initializer #%d cannot be legally placed\n", i);
3276 incr_vec[i].cost = COST_INFINITE;
3277 continue;
3278 }
3279
3280 /* If the nominal stride has a different type than the recorded
3281 stride type, build a cast from the nominal stride to that type. */
3282 if (!types_compatible_p (TREE_TYPE (c->stride), c->stride_type))
3283 {
3284 init_stride = make_temp_ssa_name (c->stride_type, NULL, "slsr");
3285 cast_stmt = gimple_build_assign (init_stride, NOP_EXPR, c->stride);
3286 }
3287 else
3288 init_stride = c->stride;
3289
3290 /* Create a new SSA name to hold the initializer's value. */
3291 new_name = make_temp_ssa_name (c->stride_type, NULL, "slsr");
3292 incr_vec[i].initializer = new_name;
3293
3294 /* Create the initializer and insert it in the latest possible
3295 dominating position. */
3296 incr_tree = wide_int_to_tree (c->stride_type, incr);
3297 init_stmt = gimple_build_assign (new_name, MULT_EXPR,
3298 init_stride, incr_tree);
3299 if (where)
3300 {
3301 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi = gsi_for_stmt (where->cand_stmt);
3302 location_t loc = gimple_location (where->cand_stmt);
3303
3304 if (cast_stmt)
3305 {
3306 gsi_insert_before (&gsi, cast_stmt, GSI_SAME_STMT);
3307 gimple_set_location (cast_stmt, loc);
3308 }
3309
3310 gsi_insert_before (&gsi, init_stmt, GSI_SAME_STMT);
3311 gimple_set_location (init_stmt, loc);
3312 }
3313 else
3314 {
3315 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi = gsi_last_bb (bb);
3316 gimple *basis_stmt = lookup_cand (c->basis)->cand_stmt;
3317 location_t loc = gimple_location (basis_stmt);
3318
3319 if (!gsi_end_p (gsi) && stmt_ends_bb_p (gsi_stmt (gsi)))
3320 {
3321 if (cast_stmt)
3322 {
3323 gsi_insert_before (&gsi, cast_stmt, GSI_SAME_STMT);
3324 gimple_set_location (cast_stmt, loc);
3325 }
3326 gsi_insert_before (&gsi, init_stmt, GSI_SAME_STMT);
3327 }
3328 else
3329 {
3330 if (cast_stmt)
3331 {
3332 gsi_insert_after (&gsi, cast_stmt, GSI_NEW_STMT);
3333 gimple_set_location (cast_stmt, loc);
3334 }
3335 gsi_insert_after (&gsi, init_stmt, GSI_SAME_STMT);
3336 }
3337
3338 gimple_set_location (init_stmt, gimple_location (basis_stmt));
3339 }
3340
3341 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3342 {
3343 if (cast_stmt)
3344 {
3345 fputs ("Inserting stride cast: ", dump_file);
3346 print_gimple_stmt (dump_file, cast_stmt, 0, 0);
3347 }
3348 fputs ("Inserting initializer: ", dump_file);
3349 print_gimple_stmt (dump_file, init_stmt, 0, 0);
3350 }
3351 }
3352}
3353
3354/* Return TRUE iff all required increments for candidates feeding PHI
3355 are profitable (and legal!) to replace on behalf of candidate C. */
3356
3357static bool
3358all_phi_incrs_profitable (slsr_cand_t c, gphi *phi)
3359{
3360 unsigned i;
3361 slsr_cand_t basis = lookup_cand (c->basis);
3362 slsr_cand_t phi_cand = *stmt_cand_map->get (phi);
3363
3364 /* If the basis doesn't dominate the PHI (including when the PHI is
3365 in the same block as the basis), we won't be able to create a PHI
3366 using the basis here. */
3367 basic_block basis_bb = gimple_bb (basis->cand_stmt);
3368 basic_block phi_bb = gimple_bb (phi);
3369
3370 if (phi_bb == basis_bb
3371 || !dominated_by_p (CDI_DOMINATORS, phi_bb, basis_bb))
3372 return false;
3373
3374 for (i = 0; i < gimple_phi_num_args (phi); i++)
3375 {
3376 /* If the PHI arg resides in a block not dominated by the basis,
3377 we won't be able to create a PHI using the basis here. */
3378 basic_block pred_bb = gimple_phi_arg_edge (phi, i)->src;
3379
3380 if (!dominated_by_p (CDI_DOMINATORS, pred_bb, basis_bb))
3381 return false;
3382
3383 tree arg = gimple_phi_arg_def (phi, i);
3384 gimple *arg_def = SSA_NAME_DEF_STMT (arg);
3385
3386 if (gimple_code (arg_def) == GIMPLE_PHI)
3387 {
3388 if (!all_phi_incrs_profitable (c, as_a <gphi *> (arg_def)))
3389 return false;
3390 }
3391 else
3392 {
3393 int j;
3394 widest_int increment;
3395
3396 if (operand_equal_p (arg, phi_cand->base_expr, 0))
3397 increment = -basis->index;
3398 else
3399 {
3400 slsr_cand_t arg_cand = base_cand_from_table (arg);
3401 increment = arg_cand->index - basis->index;
3402 }
3403
3404 if (!address_arithmetic_p && wi::neg_p (increment))
3405 increment = -increment;
3406
3407 j = incr_vec_index (increment);
3408
3409 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3410 {
3411 fprintf (dump_file, " Conditional candidate %d, phi: ",
3412 c->cand_num);
3413 print_gimple_stmt (dump_file, phi, 0, 0);
3414 fputs (" increment: ", dump_file);
3415 print_decs (increment, dump_file);
3416 if (j < 0)
3417 fprintf (dump_file,
3418 "\n Not replaced; incr_vec overflow.\n");
3419 else {
3420 fprintf (dump_file, "\n cost: %d\n", incr_vec[j].cost);
3421 if (profitable_increment_p (j))
3422 fputs (" Replacing...\n", dump_file);
3423 else
3424 fputs (" Not replaced.\n", dump_file);
3425 }
3426 }
3427
3428 if (j < 0 || !profitable_increment_p (j))
3429 return false;
3430 }
3431 }
3432
3433 return true;
3434}
3435
3436/* Create a NOP_EXPR that copies FROM_EXPR into a new SSA name of
3437 type TO_TYPE, and insert it in front of the statement represented
3438 by candidate C. Use *NEW_VAR to create the new SSA name. Return
3439 the new SSA name. */
3440
3441static tree
3442introduce_cast_before_cand (slsr_cand_t c, tree to_type, tree from_expr)
3443{
3444 tree cast_lhs;
3445 gassign *cast_stmt;
3446 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi = gsi_for_stmt (c->cand_stmt);
3447
3448 cast_lhs = make_temp_ssa_name (to_type, NULL, "slsr");
3449 cast_stmt = gimple_build_assign (cast_lhs, NOP_EXPR, from_expr);
3450 gimple_set_location (cast_stmt, gimple_location (c->cand_stmt));
3451 gsi_insert_before (&gsi, cast_stmt, GSI_SAME_STMT);
3452
3453 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3454 {
3455 fputs (" Inserting: ", dump_file);
3456 print_gimple_stmt (dump_file, cast_stmt, 0, 0);
3457 }
3458
3459 return cast_lhs;
3460}
3461
3462/* Replace the RHS of the statement represented by candidate C with
3463 NEW_CODE, NEW_RHS1, and NEW_RHS2, provided that to do so doesn't
3464 leave C unchanged or just interchange its operands. The original
3465 operation and operands are in OLD_CODE, OLD_RHS1, and OLD_RHS2.
3466 If the replacement was made and we are doing a details dump,
3467 return the revised statement, else NULL. */
3468
3469static gimple *
3470replace_rhs_if_not_dup (enum tree_code new_code, tree new_rhs1, tree new_rhs2,
3471 enum tree_code old_code, tree old_rhs1, tree old_rhs2,
3472 slsr_cand_t c)
3473{
3474 if (new_code != old_code
3475 || ((!operand_equal_p (new_rhs1, old_rhs1, 0)
3476 || !operand_equal_p (new_rhs2, old_rhs2, 0))
3477 && (!operand_equal_p (new_rhs1, old_rhs2, 0)
3478 || !operand_equal_p (new_rhs2, old_rhs1, 0))))
3479 {
3480 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi = gsi_for_stmt (c->cand_stmt);
3481 slsr_cand_t cc = lookup_cand (c->first_interp);
3482 gimple_assign_set_rhs_with_ops (&gsi, new_code, new_rhs1, new_rhs2);
3483 update_stmt (gsi_stmt (gsi));
3484 while (cc)
3485 {
3486 cc->cand_stmt = gsi_stmt (gsi);
3487 cc = cc->next_interp ? lookup_cand (cc->next_interp) : NULL;
3488 }
3489
3490 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3491 return gsi_stmt (gsi);
3492 }
3493
3494 else if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3495 fputs (" (duplicate, not actually replacing)\n", dump_file);
3496
3497 return NULL;
3498}
3499
3500/* Strength-reduce the statement represented by candidate C by replacing
3501 it with an equivalent addition or subtraction. I is the index into
3502 the increment vector identifying C's increment. NEW_VAR is used to
3503 create a new SSA name if a cast needs to be introduced. BASIS_NAME
3504 is the rhs1 to use in creating the add/subtract. */
3505
3506static void
3507replace_one_candidate (slsr_cand_t c, unsigned i, tree basis_name)
3508{
3509 gimple *stmt_to_print = NULL;
3510 tree orig_rhs1, orig_rhs2;
3511 tree rhs2;
3512 enum tree_code orig_code, repl_code;
3513 widest_int cand_incr;
3514
3515 orig_code = gimple_assign_rhs_code (c->cand_stmt);
3516 orig_rhs1 = gimple_assign_rhs1 (c->cand_stmt);
3517 orig_rhs2 = gimple_assign_rhs2 (c->cand_stmt);
3518 cand_incr = cand_increment (c);
3519
3520 /* If orig_rhs2 is NULL, we have already replaced this in situ with
3521 a copy statement under another interpretation. */
3522 if (!orig_rhs2)
3523 return;
3524
3525 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3526 {
3527 fputs ("Replacing: ", dump_file);
3528 print_gimple_stmt (dump_file, c->cand_stmt, 0, 0);
3529 stmt_to_print = c->cand_stmt;
3530 }
3531
3532 if (address_arithmetic_p)
3533 repl_code = POINTER_PLUS_EXPR;
3534 else
3535 repl_code = PLUS_EXPR;
3536
3537 /* If the increment has an initializer T_0, replace the candidate
3538 statement with an add of the basis name and the initializer. */
3539 if (incr_vec[i].initializer)
3540 {
3541 tree init_type = TREE_TYPE (incr_vec[i].initializer);
3542 tree orig_type = TREE_TYPE (orig_rhs2);
3543
3544 if (types_compatible_p (orig_type, init_type))
3545 rhs2 = incr_vec[i].initializer;
3546 else
3547 rhs2 = introduce_cast_before_cand (c, orig_type,
3548 incr_vec[i].initializer);
3549
3550 if (incr_vec[i].incr != cand_incr)
3551 {
3552 gcc_assert (repl_code == PLUS_EXPR);
3553 repl_code = MINUS_EXPR;
3554 }
3555
3556 stmt_to_print = replace_rhs_if_not_dup (repl_code, basis_name, rhs2,
3557 orig_code, orig_rhs1, orig_rhs2,
3558 c);
3559 }
3560
3561 /* Otherwise, the increment is one of -1, 0, and 1. Replace
3562 with a subtract of the stride from the basis name, a copy
3563 from the basis name, or an add of the stride to the basis
3564 name, respectively. It may be necessary to introduce a
3565 cast (or reuse an existing cast). */
3566 else if (cand_incr == 1)
3567 {
3568 tree stride_type = TREE_TYPE (c->stride);
3569 tree orig_type = TREE_TYPE (orig_rhs2);
3570
3571 if (types_compatible_p (orig_type, stride_type))
3572 rhs2 = c->stride;
3573 else
3574 rhs2 = introduce_cast_before_cand (c, orig_type, c->stride);
3575
3576 stmt_to_print = replace_rhs_if_not_dup (repl_code, basis_name, rhs2,
3577 orig_code, orig_rhs1, orig_rhs2,
3578 c);
3579 }
3580
3581 else if (cand_incr == -1)
3582 {
3583 tree stride_type = TREE_TYPE (c->stride);
3584 tree orig_type = TREE_TYPE (orig_rhs2);
3585 gcc_assert (repl_code != POINTER_PLUS_EXPR);
3586
3587 if (types_compatible_p (orig_type, stride_type))
3588 rhs2 = c->stride;
3589 else
3590 rhs2 = introduce_cast_before_cand (c, orig_type, c->stride);
3591
3592 if (orig_code != MINUS_EXPR
3593 || !operand_equal_p (basis_name, orig_rhs1, 0)
3594 || !operand_equal_p (rhs2, orig_rhs2, 0))
3595 {
3596 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi = gsi_for_stmt (c->cand_stmt);
3597 slsr_cand_t cc = lookup_cand (c->first_interp);
3598 gimple_assign_set_rhs_with_ops (&gsi, MINUS_EXPR, basis_name, rhs2);
3599 update_stmt (gsi_stmt (gsi));
3600 while (cc)
3601 {
3602 cc->cand_stmt = gsi_stmt (gsi);
3603 cc = cc->next_interp ? lookup_cand (cc->next_interp) : NULL;
3604 }
3605
3606 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3607 stmt_to_print = gsi_stmt (gsi);
3608 }
3609 else if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3610 fputs (" (duplicate, not actually replacing)\n", dump_file);
3611 }
3612
3613 else if (cand_incr == 0)
3614 {
3615 tree lhs = gimple_assign_lhs (c->cand_stmt);
3616 tree lhs_type = TREE_TYPE (lhs);
3617 tree basis_type = TREE_TYPE (basis_name);
3618
3619 if (types_compatible_p (lhs_type, basis_type))
3620 {
3621 gassign *copy_stmt = gimple_build_assign (lhs, basis_name);
3622 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi = gsi_for_stmt (c->cand_stmt);
3623 slsr_cand_t cc = lookup_cand (c->first_interp);
3624 gimple_set_location (copy_stmt, gimple_location (c->cand_stmt));
3625 gsi_replace (&gsi, copy_stmt, false);
3626 while (cc)
3627 {
3628 cc->cand_stmt = copy_stmt;
3629 cc = cc->next_interp ? lookup_cand (cc->next_interp) : NULL;
3630 }
3631
3632 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3633 stmt_to_print = copy_stmt;
3634 }
3635 else
3636 {
3637 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi = gsi_for_stmt (c->cand_stmt);
3638 gassign *cast_stmt = gimple_build_assign (lhs, NOP_EXPR, basis_name);
3639 slsr_cand_t cc = lookup_cand (c->first_interp);
3640 gimple_set_location (cast_stmt, gimple_location (c->cand_stmt));
3641 gsi_replace (&gsi, cast_stmt, false);
3642 while (cc)
3643 {
3644 cc->cand_stmt = cast_stmt;
3645 cc = cc->next_interp ? lookup_cand (cc->next_interp) : NULL;
3646 }
3647
3648 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3649 stmt_to_print = cast_stmt;
3650 }
3651 }
3652 else
3653 gcc_unreachable ();
3654
3655 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS) && stmt_to_print)
3656 {
3657 fputs ("With: ", dump_file);
3658 print_gimple_stmt (dump_file, stmt_to_print, 0, 0);
3659 fputs ("\n", dump_file);
3660 }
3661}
3662
3663/* For each candidate in the tree rooted at C, replace it with
3664 an increment if such has been shown to be profitable. */
3665
3666static void
3667replace_profitable_candidates (slsr_cand_t c)
3668{
3669 if (!cand_already_replaced (c))
3670 {
3671 widest_int increment = cand_abs_increment (c);
3672 enum tree_code orig_code = gimple_assign_rhs_code (c->cand_stmt);
3673 int i;
3674
3675 i = incr_vec_index (increment);
3676
3677 /* Only process profitable increments. Nothing useful can be done
3678 to a cast or copy. */
3679 if (i >= 0
3680 && profitable_increment_p (i)
3681 && orig_code != SSA_NAME
3682 && !CONVERT_EXPR_CODE_P (orig_code))
3683 {
3684 if (phi_dependent_cand_p (c))
3685 {
3686 gphi *phi = as_a <gphi *> (lookup_cand (c->def_phi)->cand_stmt);
3687
3688 if (all_phi_incrs_profitable (c, phi))
3689 {
3690 /* Look up the LHS SSA name from C's basis. This will be
3691 the RHS1 of the adds we will introduce to create new
3692 phi arguments. */
3693 slsr_cand_t basis = lookup_cand (c->basis);
3694 tree basis_name = gimple_assign_lhs (basis->cand_stmt);
3695
3696 /* Create a new phi statement that will represent C's true
3697 basis after the transformation is complete. */
3698 location_t loc = gimple_location (c->cand_stmt);
3699 tree name = create_phi_basis (c, phi, basis_name,
3700 loc, UNKNOWN_STRIDE);
3701
3702 /* Replace C with an add of the new basis phi and the
3703 increment. */
3704 replace_one_candidate (c, i, name);
3705 }
3706 }
3707 else
3708 {
3709 slsr_cand_t basis = lookup_cand (c->basis);
3710 tree basis_name = gimple_assign_lhs (basis->cand_stmt);
3711 replace_one_candidate (c, i, basis_name);
3712 }
3713 }
3714 }
3715
3716 if (c->sibling)
3717 replace_profitable_candidates (lookup_cand (c->sibling));
3718
3719 if (c->dependent)
3720 replace_profitable_candidates (lookup_cand (c->dependent));
3721}
3722
3723/* Analyze costs of related candidates in the candidate vector,
3724 and make beneficial replacements. */
3725
3726static void
3727analyze_candidates_and_replace (void)
3728{
3729 unsigned i;
3730 slsr_cand_t c;
3731
3732 /* Each candidate that has a null basis and a non-null
3733 dependent is the root of a tree of related statements.
3734 Analyze each tree to determine a subset of those
3735 statements that can be replaced with maximum benefit. */
3736 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (cand_vec, i, c)
3737 {
3738 slsr_cand_t first_dep;
3739
3740 if (c->basis != 0 || c->dependent == 0)
3741 continue;
3742
3743 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3744 fprintf (dump_file, "\nProcessing dependency tree rooted at %d.\n",
3745 c->cand_num);
3746
3747 first_dep = lookup_cand (c->dependent);
3748
3749 /* If this is a chain of CAND_REFs, unconditionally replace
3750 each of them with a strength-reduced data reference. */
3751 if (c->kind == CAND_REF)
3752 replace_refs (c);
3753
3754 /* If the common stride of all related candidates is a known
3755 constant, each candidate without a phi-dependence can be
3756 profitably replaced. Each replaces a multiply by a single
3757 add, with the possibility that a feeding add also goes dead.
3758 A candidate with a phi-dependence is replaced only if the
3759 compensation code it requires is offset by the strength
3760 reduction savings. */
3761 else if (TREE_CODE (c->stride) == INTEGER_CST)
3762 replace_uncond_cands_and_profitable_phis (first_dep);
3763
3764 /* When the stride is an SSA name, it may still be profitable
3765 to replace some or all of the dependent candidates, depending
3766 on whether the introduced increments can be reused, or are
3767 less expensive to calculate than the replaced statements. */
3768 else
3769 {
3770 machine_mode mode;
3771 bool speed;
3772
3773 /* Determine whether we'll be generating pointer arithmetic
3774 when replacing candidates. */
3775 address_arithmetic_p = (c->kind == CAND_ADD
3776 && POINTER_TYPE_P (c->cand_type));
3777
3778 /* If all candidates have already been replaced under other
3779 interpretations, nothing remains to be done. */
3780 if (!count_candidates (c))
3781 continue;
3782
3783 /* Construct an array of increments for this candidate chain. */
3784 incr_vec = XNEWVEC (incr_info, MAX_INCR_VEC_LEN);
3785 incr_vec_len = 0;
3786 record_increments (c);
3787
3788 /* Determine which increments are profitable to replace. */
3789 mode = TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (gimple_assign_lhs (c->cand_stmt)));
3790 speed = optimize_cands_for_speed_p (c);
3791 analyze_increments (first_dep, mode, speed);
3792
3793 /* Insert initializers of the form T_0 = stride * increment
3794 for use in profitable replacements. */
3795 insert_initializers (first_dep);
3796 dump_incr_vec ();
3797
3798 /* Perform the replacements. */
3799 replace_profitable_candidates (first_dep);
3800 free (incr_vec);
3801 }
3802 }
3803
3804 /* For conditional candidates, we may have uncommitted insertions
3805 on edges to clean up. */
3806 gsi_commit_edge_inserts ();
3807}

3836
3837unsigned
3838pass_strength_reduction::execute (function *fun)
3839{
3840 /* Create the obstack where candidates will reside. */
3841 gcc_obstack_init (&cand_obstack);
3842
3843 /* Allocate the candidate vector. */
3844 cand_vec.create (128);
3845
3846 /* Allocate the mapping from statements to candidate indices. */
3847 stmt_cand_map = new hash_map<gimple *, slsr_cand_t>;
3848
3849 /* Create the obstack where candidate chains will reside. */
3850 gcc_obstack_init (&chain_obstack);
3851
3852 /* Allocate the mapping from base expressions to candidate chains. */
3853 base_cand_map = new hash_table<cand_chain_hasher> (500);
3854
3855 /* Allocate the mapping from bases to alternative bases. */
3856 alt_base_map = new hash_map<tree, tree>;
3857
3858 /* Initialize the loop optimizer. We need to detect flow across
3859 back edges, and this gives us dominator information as well. */
3860 loop_optimizer_init (AVOID_CFG_MODIFICATIONS);
3861
3862 /* Walk the CFG in predominator order looking for strength reduction
3863 candidates. */
3864 find_candidates_dom_walker (CDI_DOMINATORS)
3865 .walk (fun->cfg->x_entry_block_ptr);
3866
3867 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3868 {
3869 dump_cand_vec ();
3870 dump_cand_chains ();
3871 }
3872
3873 delete alt_base_map;
3874 free_affine_expand_cache (&name_expansions);
3875
3876 /* Analyze costs and make appropriate replacements. */
3877 analyze_candidates_and_replace ();
3878
3879 loop_optimizer_finalize ();
3880 delete base_cand_map;
3881 base_cand_map = NULL;
3882 obstack_free (&chain_obstack, NULL);
3883 delete stmt_cand_map;
3884 cand_vec.release ();
3885 obstack_free (&cand_obstack, NULL);
3886
3887 return 0;
3888}
3889
3890} // anon namespace

3893make_pass_strength_reduction (gcc::context *ctxt)
3894{
3895 return new pass_strength_reduction (ctxt);
3896}
